    "top_event": "Fire in Glycol Reboiler Dehydration System",
    "incident_type": "fire",
    "costs": "100000",
    "actions_taken": [
      "Platform emergency shut down device activated",
      "Fire extinguished using four fire extinguishers (two 150-pound and two 30-pound)",
      "Glycol Reboiler Dehydration unit removed and transported to Universal Equipment Company for inspection",
      "Still column replacement campaign planned to coincide with 5-year fire tube inspection",
      "Condition assessment of all still columns across the gulf planned by end of Q1 FY23"
    ],
    "summary": "On January 5, 2023, at 1730 hours, a fire occurred in the Glycol Reboiler Dehydration system at High Island 547 B platform. The still column vent pipe became plugged, causing pressure buildup until rupture. Glycol spray contacted the reboiler and exhaust stack (operating at 750-800\u00b0F), igniting the glycol mixture. The fire was extinguished in ten minutes with no injuries or pollution. Damage exceeded $100,000.",
    "recommendations": [
      "Develop a servicing plan to inspect the Still Column Vent piping"
    ],
